\f0\fs26 \cf0 PLEASE READ:\
By default, fonts will be installed into the /Library/Keyboard Layouts folder, where they will be accessible to all users of the the system.  \
If you wish to install the keyboards so that they will only be available to the current user, click Change Install Location in the Installation Type screen, and select "Install for me only."\
\
AFTER INSTALLATION\
PLEASE EITHER LOGOUT OR RESTART YOUR COMPUTER AFTER THE INSTALL IS FINISHED.  After logging back in, the Biblical Hebrew keyboards must be enabled through the International pane of the System Preferences, the in the Input Menu.   The option "Show input menu in menu bar" should be checked.  Keyboards are available in the Input Menu.  Biblical Hebrew will appear in the list.  Any desired keyboard should be checked.  After they have been enabled there, they will be accessible in the upper right corner of the of the menu bar.  The Tiro keyboard icon is an alef, while the SIL keyboard icon is an alef with a blue diamond.\
Any questions, comments, or error reports should be emailed to christopher.hooker@sbl-site.org.\
\
\'a9 Society of Biblical Literature, 2008}]]></readme>
